Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so\N{\rChinese}好的，今天我们来讨论普京的计划，消灭美帝。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.46,0:00:07.30,English,,0,0,0,,today we will discuss Putin's plan to destroy the American Empire.\N{\rChinese}在上一节课里我们讨论了……
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.56,0:00:10.10,English,,0,0,0,,So last class we discussed that\N{\rChinese}So last class wediscussed that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.10,0:00:12.80,English,,0,0,0,,Putin loves his country, Russia,\N{\rChinese}普京热爱他的祖国俄罗斯，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.98,0:00:15.94,English,,0,0,0,,and he believes that\N{\rChinese}并且他认为西方消费主义已败坏他的国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.94,0:00:19.04,English,,0,0,0,,Western consumerism has corrupted his nation.\N{\rChinese}Western consumerism has corrupted his nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.84,0:00:21.16,English,,0,0,0,,And he recognizes that\N{\rChinese}并且他认识到
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.16,0:00:25.76,English,,0,0,0,,the source of Western consumerism is the American Empire.\N{\rChinese}西方消费主义的源头是美帝。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:29.14,English,,0,0,0,,So in order to completely free its people,\N{\rChinese}于是为彻底解放其人民，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.32,0:00:32.32,English,,0,0,0,,he needs to destroy the empire.\N{\rChinese}他需要摧毁帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.88,0:00:34.26,English,,0,0,0,,And historically,\N{\rChinese}而且在历史上，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.72,0:00:37.48,English,,0,0,0,,empires die when\N{\rChinese}帝国在...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.48,0:00:40.68,English,,0,0,0,,three things happen concurrently, together.\N{\rChinese}三件事同时发生，合在一起。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.30,0:00:46.56,English,,0,0,0,,The first is overextension.\N{\rChinese}第一件是过度扩张。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.60,0:00:51.44,English,,0,0,0,,And this is the main reason why empires die,\N{\rChinese}这正是帝国衰亡的主要原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.66,0:00:55.56,English,,0,0,0,,when they fight too many wars at once.\N{\rChinese}当他们一次打太多场战争时。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.60,0:01:00.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And the reason why they're overextended is hubris.\N{\rChinese}好的。它们过度扩张的原因是自负。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.62,0:01:06.64,English,,0,0,0,,And what hubris is in military strategy is the idea of blindness.\N{\rChinese}在军事战略里，自负就是盲目。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.42,0:01:14.94,English,,0,0,0,,So you are blind to the fact of your own limitations.\N{\rChinese}于是你对自身局限一无所知。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.40,0:01:19.82,English,,0,0,0,,You are blind to the strategy of your opponents.\N{\rChinese}你对对手的战略一无所见。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.64,0:01:25.20,English,,0,0,0,,You are blind to the overall geopolitical picture.\N{\rChinese}你对整体地缘政治图景一无所知。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.26,0:01:26.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. You're just blind.\N{\rChinese}好的。你刚才才是盲目。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.08,0:01:30.68,English,,0,0,0,,And the example is American strategy nowadays,\N{\rChinese}而例子是现在的美式战略，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.10,0:01:34.90,English,,0,0,0,,where America is fighting Russia and Ukraine,\N{\rChinese}美国正与俄乌交战。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.70,0:01:39.58,English,,0,0,0,,where it is fighting Hamas in Israel,\N{\rChinese}在以色列打哈马斯，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.82,0:01:43.24,English,,0,0,0,,and there's a threat of Iran on the horizon.\N{\rChinese}还有伊朗的威胁在天际。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.88,0:01:46.32,English,,0,0,0,,But for whatever reason,\N{\rChinese}但不管怎样原因，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.50,0:01:49.98,English,,0,0,0,,most American policymakers believe\N{\rChinese}大多数美国决策者认为
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.98,0:01:51.64,English,,0,0,0,,that the real threat is China.\N{\rChinese}真正的威胁是中国。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.98,0:01:55.60,English,,0,0,0,,We must prepare for China in Taiwan.\N{\rChinese}我们必须为中国在台湾做准备。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.60,0:01:56.96,English,,0,0,0,,And if we don't, then Taiwan is straight. Okay?\N{\rChinese}如果我们不这么做，台湾就会直接落入手中。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.04,0:02:01.54,English,,0,0,0,,Eventually, China will invade Taiwan, and we must be ready.\N{\rChinese}最终，中国会入侵台湾，我们必须做好准备。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.38,0:02:06.36,English,,0,0,0,,Right now, this week,\N{\rChinese}现在这周，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.46,0:02:11.48,English,,0,0,0,,America also announced massive tariffs on Chinese electrical vehicles.\N{\rChinese}美国还宣布对中国电动车征收大额关税。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.30,0:02:18.72,English,,0,0,0,,And so America is engaged in all these wars at once.\N{\rChinese}于是美国同时卷入了所有这些战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.08,0:02:20.60,English,,0,0,0,,It's antagonizing Russia,\N{\rChinese}它正与俄罗斯对峙，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.00,0:02:23.88,English,,0,0,0,,Iran, China at the same time.\N{\rChinese}伊朗、中国同时如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.88,0:02:28.16,English,,0,0,0,,And so that's just overextension because of hubris.\N{\rChinese}于是这就是因自大而导致的过度扩张。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.94,0:02:31.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Um, second,\N{\rChinese}好的？嗯，第二个，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.86,0:02:34.64,English,,0,0,0,,second way to kill an empire is debt.\N{\rChinese}第二种消灭帝国的方式是债务。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.78,0:02:40.94,English,,0,0,0,,So the source of American power is the US dollar.\N{\rChinese}于是美国力量的源泉是美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.66,0:02:45.08,English,,0,0,0,,Remember that in 1945, Bretton Woods,\N{\rChinese}记住，1945年布雷顿森林会议，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.28,0:02:49.92,English,,0,0,0,,there was an agreement that the US dollar would become the reserve currency of the world, okay?\N{\rChinese}那时约定美元成为世界储备货币，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.92,0:02:53.88,English,,0,0,0,,And the word, the phrase for that is exorbitant privilege.\N{\rChinese}并且这个词、这个短语是“过度特权”。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.50,0:02:58.20,English,,0,0,0,,Exorbitant privilege just means that\N{\rChinese}过度特权就是指……
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.20,0:03:01.32,English,,0,0,0,,America has the right\N{\rChinese}美国拥有从无中制造黄金的权利。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.32,0:03:04.88,English,,0,0,0,,to manufacture gold from nothing.\N{\rChinese}而世界则必须去购买。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.98,0:03:07.08,English,,0,0,0,,And the world has to buy it because\N{\rChinese}And the world has to buy it because
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:10.00,English,,0,0,0,,that's what underpins global trade.\N{\rChinese}这就是全球贸易的基础。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.74,0:03:13.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But when you can do that,\N{\rChinese}好吧？但当你能做到这一点时，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.54,0:03:15.44,English,,0,0,0,,what happens eventually is that\N{\rChinese}最终会发生的事是
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.44,0:03:19.22,English,,0,0,0,,your nation becomes fat,\N{\rChinese}你的国家变得肥大，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:21.98,English,,0,0,0,,rich, and lazy, and corrupt.\N{\rChinese}富裕，懒散，腐败。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.56,0:03:26.24,English,,0,0,0,,When money just falls off the sky,\N{\rChinese}当钱从天而降时。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.68,0:03:31.10,English,,0,0,0,,you're just used to borrowing money, okay?\N{\rChinese}你刚刚习惯借钱，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.26,0:03:35.10,English,,0,0,0,,So all America does right now is print money and not make money.\N{\rChinese}于是美国现在做的事就是印钱不造钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.06,0:03:38.10,English,,0,0,0,,The problem with this is that\N{\rChinese}这件事的难点在于…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.10,0:03:43.52,English,,0,0,0,,eventually the world is not going to want the US dollars anymore\N{\rChinese}最终世界将不再需要美元
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.52,0:03:48.18,English,,0,0,0,,because each time you use it, you're being taxed, right, by the Americans.\N{\rChinese}每次使用美元，都是被美国人征税
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.50,0:03:49.88,English,,0,0,0,,And that's what breaks the law.\N{\rChinese}这就是破坏规律的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.90,0:03:53.06,English,,0,0,0,,So what's the BRICS Plus? You may have heard of BRICS Plus.\N{\rChinese}那BRICS Plus到底是什么？你可能听说过BRICS Plus。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.28,0:03:58.08,English,,0,0,0,,It is an organization established initially by Brazil,\N{\rChinese}它最初是由巴西、俄国、印、华、南组成的组织。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.46,0:04:01.32,English,,0,0,0,,Russia, India, China, and South\N{\rChinese}Russia, India, China, and South
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.86,0:04:04.30,English,,0,0,0,,Africa in order to create its\N{\rChinese}非洲为此创建自己的金融体系，以对抗美国金融体系。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:08.82,English,,0,0,0,,own financial system to counter the US financial system.\N{\rChinese}但现在已有更多国家加入了金砖。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.04,0:04:12.76,English,,0,0,0,,But now there are more countries that have joined BRICS.\N{\rChinese}But now there are more countries that have joined BRICS.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.88,0:04:16.66,English,,0,0,0,,Most prominently are Saudi Arabia.\N{\rChinese}最显著的是沙特阿拉伯。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.22,0:04:21.82,English,,0,0,0,,And UAE and Bahrain.\N{\rChinese}以及阿联酋和巴林。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.94,0:04:25.84,English,,0,0,0,,These countries, okay? They're important because they are the basis for the petrodollar.\N{\rChinese}这些国家，好的？它们之所以重要，是因为它们是石油美元的基础。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:30.66,English,,0,0,0,,Remember that all US dollars can be used to purchase oil,\N{\rChinese}记住，所有美元都能买油，这就是美元价值高的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.88,0:04:33.78,English,,0,0,0,,and that's why US dollar is worth a lot of money, okay?\N{\rChinese}所以如果这些国家加入金砖，就会……
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.96,0:04:36.52,English,,0,0,0,,So if these countries go to BRICS and\N{\rChinese}So if these countries go to BRICS and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.52,0:04:39.62,English,,0,0,0,,opt out of the US financial system, then basically\N{\rChinese}退出美国金融体系，随后基本上是……
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.12,0:04:43.34,English,,0,0,0,,this American mountain of debt,\N{\rChinese}这座美国债务高峰，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.42,0:04:46.48,English,,0,0,0,,okay, $3,500, $200 of debt comes crashing down.\N{\rChinese}好了，3500美元，200美元债务坍塌下来。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:50.24,English,,0,0,0,,That's the second way to kill an empire. And\N{\rChinese}那是第二种消灭帝国的方法。然后
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.24,0:04:52.56,English,,0,0,0,,the third way is\N{\rChinese}第三种方法是
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.56,0:04:56.34,English,,0,0,0,,civil dissent or\N{\rChinese}内战或
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.34,0:04:59.22,English,,0,0,0,,eternal discord.\N{\rChinese}永恒的纷争。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.26,0:05:01.26,English,,0,0,0,,Civil war, basically. And so\N{\rChinese}内战，基本上。于是
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.26,0:05:04.66,English,,0,0,0,,what we're seeing in America right now is growing political polarization,\N{\rChinese}我们现在在美国看到的就是政治极化的加剧。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.14,0:05:07.88,English,,0,0,0,,okay, between the left and the right.\N{\rChinese}好的，左右之间。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.26,0:05:10.40,English,,0,0,0,,Why this happens is that\N{\rChinese}之所以会这样是因为
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.40,0:05:16.06,English,,0,0,0,,people no longer believe the binding myths.\N{\rChinese}人们不再相信那种连结的神话。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.16,0:05:19.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And stories that\N{\rChinese}好的？还有那些建国的故事，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.50,0:05:21.02,English,,0,0,0,,build a nation, okay?\N{\rChinese}现在的年轻人不再相信了。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.98,0:05:25.26,English,,0,0,0,,Nowadays young people no longer believe that\N{\rChinese}Nowadays young peopleno longer believe that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.26,0:05:29.84,English,,0,0,0,,America is the source of good in this world.\N{\rChinese}美国是这个世界的善源。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.98,0:05:32.86,English,,0,0,0,,An example why this is happening is, of course,\N{\rChinese}这件事发生的一个例子，当然是，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.88,0:05:36.50,English,,0,0,0,,because Israel right now is committing genocide\N{\rChinese}因为现在以色列正在实施大屠杀。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.34,0:05:40.48,English,,0,0,0,,in Gaza. Right now Israel is attacking Rafa,\N{\rChinese}在加沙。现在以色列正攻击拉法，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.64,0:05:44.36,English,,0,0,0,,and they're killing a lot of children.\N{\rChinese}他们正在杀死许多孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:46.64,English,,0,0,0,,Most people who are dying in this war are children.\N{\rChinese}这场战争中死去的多是孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.66,0:05:50.28,English,,0,0,0,,And America is not doing anything to stop this.\N{\rChinese}美国也没有做任何事来阻止这一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.36,0:05:53.60,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, America is the one who is providing the issue of all the weapons.\N{\rChinese}事实上，美国才是把所有武器送到现场的那一方。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.04,0:06:00.00,English,,0,0,0,,So young people are turning against the idea of America as the good empire.\N{\rChinese}于是年轻人开始把美国从善帝国的形象里抛出去。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.78,0:06:04.64,English,,0,0,0,,And there's this amazing statistic that\N{\rChinese}还有一个惊人的统计数据
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.64,0:06:09.66,English,,0,0,0,,one quarter of young Americans now believe\N{\rChinese}四分之一的年轻美国人现在认为
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.66,0:06:13.68,English,,0,0,0,,that Osama bin Laden was a good guy.\N{\rChinese}奥萨马·本·拉登是个好人。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.88,0:06:16.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Okay? And, you know, when I grew up,\N{\rChinese}好的？好的？而且，你知道，当我长大时，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.44,0:06:19.34,English,,0,0,0,,Osama bin Laden was considered Satan because\N{\rChinese}奥萨马·本·拉登被认为是撒旦，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.34,0:06:24.08,English,,0,0,0,,he was the one who was responsible for terrorism around the world and for the 9 -11 attacks.\N{\rChinese}他是负责全球恐怖主义和9‑11袭击的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.64,0:06:27.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But this just shows you that\N{\rChinese}好的？但这只是向你展示
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.00,0:06:31.74,English,,0,0,0,,the ideas and the myths that bind the country together are falling apart.\N{\rChinese}想法与神话将国家团结在一起的东西正要散落。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.26,0:06:34.62,English,,0,0,0,,And that's what's causing the nation to fall apart.\N{\rChinese}这就是导致民族国家分崩的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:38.86,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the more overcommitted America is,\N{\rChinese}好吧？美国越过度投入，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:42.18,English,,0,0,0,,the more debt it creates\N{\rChinese}它产生的债务越多
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.18,0:06:44.28,English,,0,0,0,,and the more civil discord.\N{\rChinese}而且民间纷争越多
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.28,0:06:46.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right?\N{\rChinese}好吧？一切都好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.84,0:06:50.70,English,,0,0,0,,So this is how you kill an empire. When all three things reach a tipping point,\N{\rChinese}于是这就是消灭帝国的方法。当三件事都达到临界点时，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.78,0:06:52.84,English,,0,0,0,,when it becomes too much, the empire dies.\N{\rChinese}当它过度时，帝国就会消亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.14,0:06:58.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the most likely outcome for America is it goes into civil war.\N{\rChinese}好吧？美国最可能的结果就是内战。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.76,0:07:00.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It descends into civil war.\N{\rChinese}好吧？它降入内战。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.62,0:07:02.70,English,,0,0,0,,And that's something that I will discuss next class.\N{\rChinese}这点我将在下节课讨论。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.26,0:07:04.76,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.76,0:07:08.68,English,,0,0,0,,let's discuss how Putin is doing this.\N{\rChinese}让我们来讨论普京是怎么做的。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.88,0:07:12.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the first thing that Putin did was the Ukraine war.\N{\rChinese}好吧？普京先做的事就是发动乌克兰战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.90,0:07:15.06,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So in February 2022,\N{\rChinese}对吧？于是2022年二月，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.76,0:07:18.74,English,,0,0,0,,Putin invaded Ukraine.\N{\rChinese}普京入侵乌克兰。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.14,0:07:22.68,English,,0,0,0,,And at that time, America was confident\N{\rChinese}当时，美国很有信心
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.68,0:07:25.08,English,,0,0,0,,that three things would happen.\N{\rChinese}那三件事会发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.18,0:07:28.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The first thing that would happen is that\N{\rChinese}好的？第一件事会是……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.38,0:07:32.74,English,,0,0,0,,Ukraine would destroy the Russian army\N{\rChinese}乌克兰将摧毁俄军
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.74,0:07:37.04,English,,0,0,0,,and perhaps even march to Moscow and overthrow Putin.\N{\rChinese}并且可能进军莫斯科，推翻普京。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.16,0:07:41.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? At that time, that's what the news media was reporting.\N{\rChinese}好的？当时，新闻媒体就是这么报道的。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.34,0:07:44.26,English,,0,0,0,,The Ukraine media was so much stronger and more confident.\N{\rChinese}乌克兰媒体更加强大，信心十足。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.28,0:07:45.76,English,,0,0,0,,And the Russian forces.\N{\rChinese}以及俄军。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.62,0:07:49.82,English,,0,0,0,,The second thing was that\N{\rChinese}第二件事是……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.82,0:07:53.90,English,,0,0,0,,the Russian economy would be destroyed.\N{\rChinese}俄国经济将被摧毁。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:07:59.26,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because America was imposing sanctions on Russia.\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为美国对俄国实施制裁。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.66,0:08:03.74,English,,0,0,0,,So America, because it controls the global financial system,\N{\rChinese}于是美国，因为它掌握全球金融体系，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:06.34,English,,0,0,0,,the ability to trade,\N{\rChinese}拥有贸易能力。
